<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-DELAHOYA (Big Bear, Calif.) _ A crisis of confidence had
struck the resident of the big cedar log cabin at the corner of De
La Hoya Street and Golden Boy Avenue here in this mountain resort
town. It clung to him like a sweat-soaked T-shirt before, during
and immediately after his loss to Felix Trinidad last September,
the first loss of his professional career. But in the last six
weeks it has dissolved into the pools of sweat in the makeshift
boxing gym that he set up in the four-car garage that sits 50 feet
from the main house. By Timothy W. Smith.
</P>
