<HEADLINE>
SHAQ STRUGGLES ON OFFENSE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA -- Shaquille O'Neal put the finish on a victory
Sunday after having a decidedly rough start.
</P>
<P>
   His block of Allen Iverson's 3-pointer closed out the Lakers'
victory o ver the Philadelphia 76ers. But despite being an assist
short of a triple-double, O'Neal faltered on offense, missing 13 of
22 shots from the field. He even cooled at the foul line, hitting 4
of 8.
</P>
<P>
   ``Just funny kind of rims,'' O'Neal said. ``They were just
bouncing off the rims, so I was just trying to draw and kick and
get everybody else involved.''
</P>
<P>
   He did, with a career-high-tying nine assists. And with power
forwards Robert Horry and A.C. Green combining for just four
rebounds (all by Green), O'Neal held the Lakers in the game with 16
boards.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal's only career triple-double came in Orlando, and with
blocks, not assists. He might have done it Sunday if not for
several missed shots by his teammates.
</P>
<P>
   ``None of that really matters,'' he said. ``I'm just glad that
we were able to get a win.''
</P>
<P>
   He's not worried about the shooting trouble.
</P>
<P>
   ``I never have two bad games in a row, so I'll be extra, extra
ready in New Jersey (on Tuesday). I'm just going to blame it on
`one of those days.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Ouch report: Kobe Bryant suffered a sprained index finger on his
right (shooting) hand in Orlando on Friday and received treatment
both before (electric stimulation) and after (ice) Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was bothering me,'' said Bryant, admitting it affected his
game `` a little bit. It wasn't at first until I got smacked on it.
... It'll be fine. Just use more of my legs on my shot, that's
all.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant said his latest return to Philadelphia, where he played
high sch ool ball, wasn't as big a deal as previous trips here.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was so intent on shutting everybody up (before). A lot
calmer (now) ,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   With most of his family now in L.A., Bryant only needed eight
tickets for the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's nice just to come back home and get a feel again for
Philly,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Back to routine: After giving a rare start to Derek Fisher on
Friday at Orlando, coach Phil Jackson went back to Ron Harper on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just want us to be flexible enough to do that on occasion,
that we're not so rote, and so staid in our habits that we can't
make changes in our lineup and still play well,'' Jackson said.
``(It's important for) guys to be ready to play when they come off
the bench or go back to the bench.''
</P>
<P>
   Friday's lineup change was the Lakers' first since Dec. 12, when
Devean George started in place of an ill Glen Rice.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
