<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-MAVERICKS-RAPTORS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROOKS, RODMAN PACE MAVERICKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO _ It took three chances for Dennis Rodman to get a
victory with the Dallas Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman grabbed 16 rebounds and Sean Rooks made some big-time
plays as the Mavericks knocked off Vince Carter and the Toronto
Raptors, 100-96, before a sellout crowd of 19,800 Sunday at Air
Canada Centre.
</P>
<P>
   It was the Mavericks' first victory in three tries with Rodman
in the lineup. Rodman, who was returning from a one-game
suspension, fouled out with 22 seconds left.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a very good win,'' Rodman said. ``I played very good,
didn't I?''
</P>
<P>
   Rooks, a little-used reserve center, took advantage of Rodman's
foul troubles and the absence of Shawn Bradley to play a key role
in the Mavericks gaining their sixth victory in their last seven
road games.
</P>
<P>
   Bradley missed the game with blurred vision _ he may play Monday
at Indiana _ but Rooks saw to it that the Mavericks didn't skip a
beat. Rooks scored 10 points, snatched three rebounds and blocked
four shots in 22 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Rooks had six points, three blocks and two rebounds in the
fourth quarter. Coach Don Nelson presented Rooks the game ball.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier in the fourth period, Rooks completed a three-point play
and scored another basket inside to keep the Mavericks in the game.
Then when Rodman fouled out, Rooks was put back in the game.
</P>
<P>
   Toronto's Antonio Davis missed two free throws that would have
tied the game, and Rooks rebounded the second miss. Rooks made one
of two free throws for a 99-96 lead, then came up with the game's
defensive gem when he batted away a Tracy McGrady pass intended for
Davis.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Finley picked up the loose ball and scored the game's
final point seconds later on a free throw. And, just for good
measure, Rooks swatted away a Muggsy Bogues drive in the waning
seconds.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was just good to be out on the floor,'' said Rooks, who
didn't play in the previous three games. ``I'm always watching the
games, so it's just good that someone had a little bit of
confidence in me today.''
</P>
<P>
   The confidence of the Mavericks continues to soar as they chase
Minnesota for the eighth playoff spot in the Western Conference.
The Timberwolves lost Sunday to New Jersey, 91-89, so the Mavericks
are six games behind Minnesota. The Denver Nuggets are one game
ahead of the Mavericks.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was an unexpected win here,'' Nelson said. ``We were
worried about this game. The blending of our team is starting to
come together. Both Rooks and Dennis Rodman stepped it up
defensively.''
</P>
<P>
   Cedric Ceballos scored eight of his 23 points in the second
period to help the Mavericks erase a 10-point deficit. Finley
shared game-high scoring honors with Ceballos with 23 points.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm fired up every day,'' Finley said. ``Whether it's Vince
Carter or Jack Haley, I'm going to go in there and give 110
percent. He's a good player and he's been playing great ball all
year. We just didn't want to get him going, and we didn't.''
</P>
<P>
   Erick Strickland and Finley closely guarded Carter, who scored
24 points and had five rebounds and seven assists before fouling
out with 35.1 seconds left and the Mavericks ahead, 96-95.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think I did anything significant, except try to make
him take tough shots,'' said Strickland, who finished with 18
points. ``He made some shots, too.
</P>
<P>
   ``But in the crucial part of the game I made him take some tough
shots and we got some breaks and some rebounds and that helped us
to pull ahead.''
</P>
<P>
   Most of the pulling away resulted from the unexpected play of
Rooks.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who knows what this proves?'' Rooks said. ``Shawn is out right
now, so I'm just going to fill in.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know what's going on. I just try to go out there and
help our guys out, and I'm very happy that things turned out the
way they turned out. They could have turned out a lot worst for
me.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
