<SLUG> BC-TECH-ANNOY22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Home intercoms make you want to scream
 &HT;    By Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ We're all for improving family communications,
but sticking a home intercom system in every bedroom and paging the
family down for dinner wins our annoying gadget of the week award.
</P>
<P>
   Eschewing traditional foot-stair movement in favor of calling
people in your own house is not only lazy, it's usually accompanied
by a squawking burst of feedback caused by having the intercom
units placed too closely together. For centuries, families have
been held together by one common denominator that crosses all
racial, cultural and generational lines: really loud yelling. If
you want the kids to come downstairs for dinner, bang on the wall
and yell their names at high decibels.
</P>
<P>
   Inter-home primal-scream therapy has kept us sane for this long.
Don't let technology take away your right to scream.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
