<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    What a girl wants: Grammys
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The genie in Christina Aguilera's bottle must have amnesia.
Instead of granting the standard three wishes, it provided the
19-year-old pop singer with a lifetime of achievements.
</P>
<P>
   First, in June of 1998 the former ``New Mickey Mouse Club''
member took a bow on the ``Mulan'' soundtrack, performing
``Reflection.''
</P>
<P>
   That led to a record deal and the 1999 summer release of her
album ``Christina Aguilera.'' It has sold more than 5 million
copies.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday, Aguilera could take home two Grammy Awards. She's up
for Best New Artist and Best Female Pop Vocal Performance Recording
for the single ``Genie in a Bottle.''
</P>
<P>
   On her way to a concert in Washington, D.C.,
</P>
<P>
   Aguilera found a moment to talk:
</P>
<P>
   Q: Would a Grammy Award just be more icing on an incredible year
for you?
</P>
<P>
   A: So many of my dreams have come true already, and I am so
appreciative. Yes! Yes! A Grammy would be a great thing. But in so
many ways, I already feel like I've won.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How did you feel at the American Music Awards when you sang
in front of your vocal inspiration, Mariah Carey?
</P>
<P>
   A: She had a seat in the front row, but she wasn't there when I
performed. And, you know, I'm glad you said ``vocal inspiration''
because she is that. But I want people to see me, not her. That
night I was so focused on people hearing what I could do live. I
don't want to be just another teen act.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What do you think about the sexiness of so many teen acts out
now?
</P>
<P>
   A: It's kind of all in how people take it. Like, I know what I
meant by ``rub me the right way'' (in ``Genie in a Bottle'') _
treat me right _ but people took it to mean something else. As long
as my intentions are good, that's my concern.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
