<P>
   LIMBS _ ATLANTA _ Two Atlantans will be getting new artificial
limbs, the first with a computer controlled knee. The C-Leg system
provides better balance and movement and is supposed to
automatically adjust to different walking speeds. It costs $30,000,
compared to about $8,000 for a typical artificial leg. One of the
recipients is a 35 year old woman who lost a limb to cancer at age
17, and hopes she'll be able to play tennis again; the other is a
40ish man who was injured in a work-related accident.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, graphic of how the leg works. (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
