   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ George W. Bush's big win in South Carolina
revived his candidacy but at the cost of the inclusive campaign
that had been the high promise of his early run for the Republican
presidential nomination. (Teepen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
