   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ Ohio's state board of education has been
meeting to review a list of what educators believe high school
seniors need to know in order to pass a 12th-grade proficiency
test. Proposed questions in the citizenship section of this test
would require students to ``illustrate how the evolution of
democratic principles (e.g., civil rights widening franchise) can
occur through civil disobedience.'' (Schuett, Cox News Service)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ Some television shows
possess the simple hypnotic drawing power of a bad car wreck.
People see something horrible happening to other people and yet
they can't look away. Even people who possess good intentions, love
for humanity and average decency cannot fail to slow down and
point. ``Who Wants to Marry a Multimillionaire?'' is car-wreck
television. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Vietnam was a tortuous groping
through alien lands. But in complexity and intractability, the drug
war makes that war look like red coats vs. blue coats, wide-open
knoll, at 40 paces. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
