<HEADLINE>
BUICK, WOODS DRIVE ON; RENDEZVOUS SUV INTRODUCED 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (l and f coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By BILL GRIFFITH  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The folks at Buick must have been giddy with joy over the
increased interest Tiger Woods brought to the Buick Invitational
golf tournament in San Diego last week.
</P>
<P>
   National media attention was focused on the tournament as Woods
made his run at an astounding seventh straight PGA Tour victory _
he finished in a tie for second after briefly tying for the lead _
on the very weekend Buick was introducing three television
commercials featuring Woods.
</P>
<P>
   The spots are the first Woods has made with the carmaker since
signing an endorsement deal in December. They hit the airwaves even
as Woods was gaining ground on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tiger and Buick are a natural combination,'' says Anthony H.
Derhake, Buick's golf brand manager. ``Tiger broadens our audience
appeal, and we expect to attract new customers to Buick as a
result. This also reinforces Buick's recognized strong connection
with golf.''
</P>
<P>
   The spots have serious and comic overtones.
</P>
<P>
   The serious commercial features Buick's support of the Tiger
Woods Foundation to bring golf to inner-city children. In it, a
grandfather helps his grandson line up _ and sink _ a putt on a
city sidewalk. Talk about fast greens!
</P>
<P>
   In another, Woods banks a shot off a TV tower supporting two
doubting announcers, dropping them into a water hazard, then offers
them a towel as he drives off, er Regal-ly. The third shows Woods
teaching adult campers how to play golf and ``drive'' the way he
does _ in a Buick of course. For Buick, the jackpot was earned.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of Buick
</P>
<P>
   The GM Division introduced its Rendezvous SUV at last week's
Chicago Auto Show. It's the first Buick truck model in 77 years.
Buick didn't put a price on it, but best guesses are it will sell
for less than $30,000, well below the similar-sized Lexus RX 300
and Mercedes M-Class. Like its GM sibling, the Pontiac Aztek, it
will offer a 185-horsepower V6 engine with optional all-wheel drive
on demand. A third row of seats can make this a seven-passenger
vehicle, or the third seat can fold flat for storage.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Most manufactures were showing off their four-door compact
pickups at the Chicago show _ except Ford, GM, Toyota, Nissan all
arrived with their new models with four regular-sized doors.
</P>
<P>
   The next day Ford unveiled its 2001 Ranger _ the country's
top-selling compact pickup for the past 13 years. It had two
regular doors and two mini-doors.
</P>
<P>
   Miracle or madness?
</P>
<P>
   Ford truck boss Jim O'Connor said Ford already has its Explorer
Sport Trac (a four-door SUV with a short pickup bed) in production
and almost ready for the showrooms.
</P>
<P>
   Even though Ford takes great pains to separate pickups from
SUVs, the inference is obvious: Want four doors? Try the Sport
Trac.
</P>
<P>
   Obviously, Ford is hesitant to hurt interest in this ballyhooed
SUV; question is, will Ranger sales suffer in that effort?
</P>
<P>
   Still, Ranger comes in enough body and door styles with both
two- and four-wheel drive to have plenty of appeal.
</P>
<P>
   O'Connor doesn't sound too upset. Ford this month forecast that
it would sell 17 million vehicles in the United States this year _
up from its original goal of 16.1 million units. And this after a
record-breaking 1999. Pickup trucks, minivans, and SUVs account for
two-thirds of Ford sales.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BMW held a winter carnival in East Rutherford, N.J., letting 100
would-be buyers experience a two-hour Ultimate Driving Experience
behind the wheel of its new $50,000 X5 Sports Activity Vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   We had a chance to try a similar trek at the New England Motor
Press Winter Driving Awards several weeks back so it's a lock that
those lucky 100 had a great time, even though they were accompanied
by a professional driver.
</P>
<P>
   BMW has a simple plan for tracking the program's success. It
will match the names of participants against future buyers.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Well, we have platinum series credit cards, so why not a
Platinum Series Lexus? The company has introduced a Platinum series
LS 400 premium luxury sedan ($55,969), GS 400 sport luxury sedan
($49,894), S 300 sport luxury sedan ($42,344) and an ES300
affordable luxury sedan at $34,924.
</P>
<P>
   The series feature special paint colors, enhanced interiors,
distinctive wheels and badging, and are well-equipped (read loaded)
with factory options. Plus, Lexus will toss in a two-year American
Express Platinum Card.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   All the Hondas I've had experience with were clean-running
vehicles. But the company is doing more. The 2000 Accord EX has
become the first car sold with California's Super Ultra Low
Emission Vehicle (SULEV) certification. (It will be priced $100
over the Accord it replaces.) The SULEV standards are the world's
strictest and go into effect beginning with the 2004 model year.
According to the California Air Resources Board, a SULEV engine
emits only 2.3 pounds of hydrocarbons during 100,000 miles of
driving, roughly the same as spilling a quart of gasoline.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DaimlerChrysler's PT Cruiser, introduced as a concept car a year
ago, is just now in production in Mexico. It will be available this
spring and priced at $16,000 (including destination charge) with
the top-end Limited model coming in at $19,995. The car is
intriguing because it boasts full-size car interior space in a
compact body. (It's built on the Neon platform).
</P>
<P>
   Outgoing DaimlerChrysler chairman Robert J. Eaton may be right
when he said, ``There isn't a cooler truck _ or car _ available
anywhere for the price.''
</P>
<P>
   Kudos to D/C for its ``Fit for a Kid'' program that offers free
public child safety seat inspections. Anyone who has purchased a
family vehicle with an eye towards its safety features owes it to
themselves to take advantage of this offer by calling their local
dealer or clicking on www.fitforakid.org. An inspection takes 20 to
30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodge folks will continue to expand their R/T lineup with a
Stratus R/T coupe with a 200-horsepower V-6 engine, specially tuned
suspension, and 17-inch performance tires. It also will be
available with a five-speed manual.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
