<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MUSIC-MADONNA-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DON'T OVERTHINK IT, JUST LISTEN TO MADONNA'S `AMERICAN PIE'  

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)   ``The Next Best Thing''; Music from the Motion Picture; Maverick) 
 
By MICHAEL D. CLARK 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Be it the big screen or the spinning disc, when it comes to the
upcoming movie ``The Next Best Thing,'' only one person apparently
matters.
</P>
<P>
   Madonna.
</P>
<P>
   For months there's been buzz about the Material Girl playing a
regular Jane who conceives a baby with her gay best friend. That
friend is Rupert Everett, but at this point, he's been something of
a side note.
</P>
<P>
   Same goes with the soundtrack.
</P>
<P>
   There are 12 tracks of interesting, multilingual, bass-heavy
dance grooves on ``The Next Best Thing,'' but the only one most
seem to care about is the Boy Toy's remake of Don McLean's
``American Pie.''
</P>
<P>
   Truth is, Madonna's electronic, William Orbit-ized cover of
``the day the music died'' isn't bad musically. She's clipped the
lyrics and replaced McLean's innocent guitar strumming with a close
encounter of the synthesized kind, but her voice is infinitely more
listenable than that of the '70s folkie.
</P>
<P>
   The unsettling question for Madonna fans should be why she did
it. After 17 years of pushing the boundaries of pop and being the
trendsetter, why fall back on a twee oater that was previously
covered by the Brady Bunch? McLean recorded it as a tribute to the
death of Buddy Holly, which certainly has no relation to ``The Next
Best Thing'' story line.
</P>
<P>
   Before overthinking it, check out some of the CD's other tracks.
``Boom Boom Ba'' by Metisse is Euro-chic rave music, sung in French
for a sexy edge. And Olive's drum-machine version of the 10cc disco
hit ``I'm Not In Love'' has rescued that song f bargain
rack. Manu Chao's ``Bongo Bongo'' makes him the Latin lover Lou
Bega would love to be.
</P>
<P>
   The real Madonna-esque song here is Mandalay's ``This Life,''
which could sit next to a ballad like ``Rain'' or ``Take a Bow'' on
her greatest-hits disc. It makes one wonder how healthy it is when
others are doing Madonna better then Ms. Ciccone herself.
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 2 1/2 stars
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
RECORDING RATINGS &QL; 
 &QL; 
4 stars _ Excellent &QL; 
3 stars _ Good &QL; 
2 stars _ Fair &QL; 
1 star _ Poor &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY XXXX &QL;
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
