<HEADLINE>
`DR. CALIGARI' A CLASSIC; `LOVERS' STUNNING BUT LONG 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari'' (1919) _ For many
decades, this great example of German Expressionism was available
only in cheesy, scratchy 16mm prints. This digitally remastered
version of Robert Wiene's silent classic features a provocative new
score by Timothy Brock.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Lovers on the Bridge'' _ Juliette Binoche plays a homeless
artist meandering through the streets of Paris while going blind in
director Leos Carax's stylish bit of melancholy. While it's
fascinating to watch Carax's stunning imagery, it's tough to stay
tuned for more than two hours.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tail Lights Fade'' _ This Canadian road movie begs, borrows,
and steals from the popular hardtop genre. Nothing original in this
race from Toronto to Vancouver. Director Malcolm Ingram needs to
rely less on talk and more on action.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Designated Mourner'' _ Playwright David Hare turns movie
director. Movie director Mike Nichols turns film actor.
Actor-playwright Wallace Shawn's play remains wonderfully
stagebound as three actors take turns talking directly into the
camera. It's an intoxicating exercise for people who appreciated
another Shawn collaboration _ ``My Dinner With Andre.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: ``American Pie'' hit the record books last week when
Universal Home Video shipments peaked at 1 million discs. . . .
Larry Hayes, founder and CEO of Ventura Entertainment, announced a
six-picture DVD deal with Our Productions to better serve the
Latino market. On Feb. 29, the distributor will release ``No
Mothers Crying, No Babies Dying'' starring Danny Trejo and Mike
Moroff. . . . InsideDVD _ a magazine devoted to news, interviews,
and reviews dealing with DVDs _ is available only on DVD. The
magazine is available free through the Web site www.insidedvd.com.
. . . Last December marked a 232 percent increase in DVD players
sold, according to a survey of the Consumer Electronics
Manufacturers Association as reported by Video Business magazine.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Feb. 29: ``Stigmata'' (DVD), ``Random
Hearts'' (DVD), ``The Suburbans'' (DVD), ``One Man's Hero'' (DVD).
March 7: ``Eyes Wide Shut'' (DVD), ``The Mirror'' (DVD), ``King of
Masks'' (DVD), ``Crime and Punishment.'' March 14: ``Outside
Providence,'' ``Guinevere,'' ``The Love Bug,'' ``Bandits'' (DVD),
``The Prophecy 3.'' March 21: ``Jakob the Liar'' (American version;
on DVD), ``The Limey,'' ``Endurance,'' ``Horror Express'' (DVD),
``Velocity Trap'' (DVD), ``Swing.'' March 28: ``Voices From a
Locked Room.'' April 4: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom
Menace,'' ``Boys Don't Cry.''
</P>
</TEXT>
