   IRISH TRAVELLERS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Five young cousins killed last month in a
horrific accident on Interstate 30 died as they lived: close
together, of necessity as much as fraternity. The accident shocked
the public, but questions arose when authorities learned that none
of the boys were older than 14 and four of them were carrying false
driver's licenses that misrepresented their age. Attempts to gather
details about the youths have led to a fragmented mosaic of the
culture from which they came: All were children of Irish Travellers
_ secretive descendants of 19th century nomads who speak an archaic
dialect, marry within the clan and specialize in home improvement
and business repair work. By MELODY MCDONALD. Story has moved in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
