   BKC-NCAA _ St. John's Erick Barkley is suspended three games for
exchanging cars with a friend. Michigan star Jamal Crawford is
suspended and ordered to reimburse $15,000 to a wealthy friend of
his family, who helped him growing up. Both Missouri's Kareem Rush
and his brother, JaRon, sat out games for acceptings gifts from AAU
coaches. All this season. Coincidence? Mike Krzyzewski wonders. The
Duke coach also wonders why the NCAA suspends players first and
asks questions later. His solution: College basketball needs its
own governing body. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
