   Macy Gray
</P>
<P>
   Kid Rock
</P>
<P>
   Britney Spears
</P>
<P>
   Susan Tedeschi
</P>
<P>
   And the winner will be: Christina Aguilera. Unless, of course, a
``Shakespeare In Love'' vs. ``Saving Private Ryan'' situation
arises and Macy Gray's highbrow beats out Mariah2000's mass appeal.
</P>
<P>
   BEST FEMALE POP VOCAL PERFORMANCE
</P>
<P>
   ``Genie In A Bottle,'' Christina Aguilera
</P>
<P>
   ``Beautiful Stranger,'' Madonna
</P>
<P>
   ``I Will Remember You,'' Sarah McLachlan
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank U,'' Alanis Morissette
</P>
<P>
   ``... Baby One More Time,'' Britney Spears
</P>
<P>
   And the winner will be: Christina Aguilera. This could go to
Spears as a concession for losing in all her other categories. Or
Grammy fave McLachlan, the best pure singer of this bunch, could
take it.
</P>
<P>
   BEST MALE POP VOCAL PERFORMANCE
</P>
<P>
   ``I Need To Know,'' Marc Anthony
</P>
<P>
   ``Mambo No. 5 (A Little Bit Of ...),'' Lou Bega
</P>
