</P>
<P>
   ``Fortunate,'' Maxwell
</P>
<P>
   ``Sweet Lady,'' Tyrese
</P>
<P>
   ``Staying Power,'' Barry White
</P>
<P>
   And the winner will be: R. Kelly. Will Barry White get
sentimental votes? Maybe, but not enough to beat the guy who's
still riding the anthem ``I Believe I Can Fly'' in voters' minds.
</P>
<P>
   BEST ROCK ALBUM
</P>
<P>
   ``Breakdown,'' Melissa Etheridge
</P>
<P>
   ``Significant Other,'' Limp Bizkit
</P>
<P>
   ``Echo,'' Tom Petty And The Heartbreakers
</P>
<P>
   ``Californication,'' Red Hot Chili Peppers
</P>
<P>
   ``Supernatural,'' Santana
</P>
<P>
   And the winner will be: Santana. Bet the double wide.
</P>
<P>
   BEST POP ALBUM
</P>
<P>
   ``Millennium,'' Backstreet Boys
</P>
<P>
   ``Believe,'' Cher
</P>
<P>
   ``Ricky Martin,'' Ricky Martin
</P>
<P>
   ``Mirrorball,'' Sarah McLachlan
</P>
<P>
   ``Brand New Day,'' Sting
</P>
<P>
   And the winner will be: Backstreet Boys. ``Millennium'' was the
best-selling album of 1999, which should sway those who might think
of selecting ``Mirrorball'' for credibility's sake.
</P>
<P>
   SONG OF THE YEAR (to the writer)
</P>
<P>
   ``I Want It That Way,'' Andreas Carlsson &AMP; Max Martin,
songwriters (Backstreet Boys)
</P>
<P>
   ``Livin' La Vida Loca,'' Desmond Child &AMP; Robi Rosa, songwriters
(Ricky Martin)
</P>
