<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.)  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``And then, suddenly, it became calm. And the troops started
mopping up. We thought they would just check everyone's passports.
But it was a cleansing of everything alive. They killed cattle,
dogs, people _ children and old people.''
</P>
<P>
   _SAPIYAT, a Chechen refugee, telling of a massacre she said she
witnessed.
</P>
