u f BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT &LR;      02-21 0274
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BOND-CALENDAR-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TREASURY OFFERINGS THIS WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Tuesday's auction of three- and six-month bills and two-year notes.
Monday was Presidents' Day, a federal holiday; there was no trading
in U.S. Treasury securities and no trading of futures on the
Chicago Board of Trade.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market last Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 5.56
percent, and a six-month bill was 5.73 percent. In when-issued
trading the two-year note was offered at a price to yield 6.25
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   KfW International Finance, 2 billion global five-year notes,
AAA/AAA/---. Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   TXU Europe Capital I, 20 million shares of $25 trust originated
preferred securities. Baa2/BBB_/---/. Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   US Airways, Series 2000-1, $373.6 million pass-through
certificates. Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
