<HEADLINE>
MCCAIN MINCES NO WORDS IN ATTACKS 
</HEADLINE>
  (kd) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAGINAW, Mich. _ Sen. John McCain has become more emphatic in
his attacks on the Republican establishment and its big-business
and conservative allies.
</P>
<P>
   On his campaign bus, while talking to a call-in radio show,
McCain did not mince words about Bob Jones University, the center
of Christian conservatism in South Carolina that prohibits
interracial dating. He described the university as a ``place where
I would have told them they are a bunch of idiots for having those
racial policies.''
</P>
<P>
   And with the National Smokers Alliance, a group affiliated with
the tobacco companies running advertisements against him in
Michigan, as it did in South Carolina, he said on Sunday night that
he welcomed the opposition and would fight back.
</P>
<P>
   ``Come on down, you jerks,'' he said. ``Come on down. You're the
guys who addicted our children.''
</P>
</TEXT>
