r s BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLA     02-21 0631
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS THINK DEFENSE DURING STREAK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ A road trip that began with hopes of a
5-1 record is now within two wins of a clean sweep, and the Lakers
have their defense to thank for it.
</P>
<P>
   They have faced fourth-quarter deficits in their first four
games of the trip but have locked down each time for the win _
holding opponents to an average of 19 points in the final period.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing in Orlando, they tied the game on Shaquille O'Neal's
steal and dunk in the final seconds, then held the Magic to 11
points in overtime. In Philadelphia, they sealed the game with two
blocked shots in the final 2.7 seconds.
</P>
<P>
   ``It shows that we're growing as a basketball team,'' said
veteran Ron Harper. ``We just don't rely on our offense, because we
haven't scored a lot (averaging 93.5 points in four games), but
anytime that we needed a defensive stop here and there, Shaq and
guys make plays. And I think that's good to see.''
</P>
<P>
   There's no big secret to the Lakers' defensive mindset.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the concentration,'' said coach Phil Jackson. ``They're
more concerned with defense right now than scoring.''
</P>
<P>
   The result is the Lakers have held opponents on this trip to an
average of 86.0 points and 41 percent shooting in their own arenas.
</P>
<P>
   ``Offense is always unpredictable,'' Jackson said. ``Defense is
the predictable part of your game. And for us, if we get on the
road and get a couple 30-point quarters in any game, we're plenty
satisfied that will carry us through to a win.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers, winners of seven straight, are a league-best 18-7 on
the road, 8-1 in Eastern Conference arenas.
</P>
<P>
   ``We play a great deal of our games in the second half of the
season on the road (20 out of 34 games),'' said Kobe Bryant.
</P>
<P>
   ``That can go with you or that can go against you. Right now, it
looks like it's going with us, because in the playoffs you have to
win games on the road.''
</P>
<P>
   All the Lakers need for a 6-0 road trip is victories over a pair
of struggling teams _ New Jersey (21-31) tonight and Cleveland
(21-31) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were thinking that all along,'' said Bryant, ``but we just
have to take it one game at a time. You can't even talk about (6-0)
right now, really. New Jersey had a big win (Sunday at Minnesota),
so they're going to be at home with a lot of momentum.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Homecoming week: Going home has been a rousing success for
the Lakers _ Jackson won in his return to Chicago, Glen Rice won in
his return to Charlotte, O'Neal won in his return to Orlando and
Bryant won in his return to hometown Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've had a game for everybody so far,'' Jackson said. ``I'll
have to manufacture something in New Jersey.''
</P>
<P>
   Actually, Jackson finished his playing career with the Nets more
than 20 years ago, then served as an assistant coach here for three
seasons. And O'Neal's roots include New Jersey as well.
</P>
<P>
   As for Cleveland, well, Harper did play the first three-plus
seasons of his career there.
</P>
<P>
   __ Pushing it: Jackson responded playfully when asked if
O'Neal's recent hot foul shooting (45 for his last 62) would change
the Lakers' strategy.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking at it as an offensive weapon now. If they go foul
Shaq at the end of a game, we've got ourselves a real strategic
victory right there,'' he quipped. ``I already asked him to shoot a
technical. He turned me down. He's not quite ready for that.''
</P>
<P>
   In fact, O'Neal's done it before, in this city. Two years ago,
he had 49 points against the Nets when coach Del Harris sent O'Neal
to the line to shoot a technical late in the fourth quarter. O'Neal
swished it for his 50th point, his high as a Laker.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-21-00 2134EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
