   At the Peabody, still a Memphis, Tenn., institution, future
president Harry Truman wrote a letter to his wife, dated Nov. 16,
1941, that reads: ``I got up at 7:15 a.m. and had breakfast in the
coffee shop downstairs, and they charged me 55 cents for tomato
